data.body:
Hi,
we noticed that the Accelerometer is not working properly on iOS 7+
Here the quick fix. I post the code here, pr request is too complex for a single line fix! :)

The value of data passed by the event handler seems to have a delay.The clue is to read directly the motionManager.AccelerometerData.

this method replace the one in the iOS\Devices\Sensors\Accelerometer.cs

```
    private void ReadingChangedHandler(CMAccelerometerData data, NSError error)
    {
        AccelerometerReading reading = new AccelerometerReading();
        this.IsDataValid = error == null;
        if (this.IsDataValid)
        {
            this.IsDataValid = true;
            //reading.Acceleration = new Vector3((float)data.Acceleration.X, (float)data.Acceleration.Y, (float)data.Acceleration.Z);
            CMAcceleration acceleration = motionManager.AccelerometerData.Acceleration;
            reading.Acceleration = new Vector3((float)acceleration.X, (float)acceleration.Y, (float)acceleration.Z);
            reading.Timestamp = DateTime.Now;
            this.CurrentValue = reading;
            this.IsDataValid = error == null;
        }
    }
```
